  "number": 331,
  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/331",
  "title": "New widget: hitsPerPageSelector",
  "body": "Based on discussion in #317. We would need a widget in the same vein as the `indexSelector` that will let the us change the number of results displayed.\n\n![image](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/283419/10664972/ef7f13c4-78c7-11e5-9761-75c94cdf5280.png)\n\nWould have the same API as the `indexSelector`, but instead of passing a list of `indices`, we'll pass a list of `hitsPerPage` (if you have a better naming, shoot).\n## API\n\n``` js\nsearch.addWidget(\n  instantsearch.widgets.hitsPerPageSelector({\n    container: '#hits-per-page-selector',\n    options: [\n      {value: 10, label: '10 results'},\n      {value: 50, label: '50 results'},\n      {value: 100, label: '100 results'},\n    ]\n  })\n);\n```\n\nNo template to pass, BEM styling added to the `select` and `option`s.\n## TODO\n- [ ] Find a better name than `hitsPerPageSelector`\n- [x] Find a better name than `hitsPerPage` attribute (`options`)\n- [ ] Update doc to warn than displaying 1000 items is a bad idea\n",
  "created_at": "2015-10-22T12:25:17Z",
